text: Jeanette Mary Fitzsimons (17 January 1945 â€“ 5 March 2020) was a New Zealand politician and environmentalist. She was the co-leader of the Green Party of Aotearoa New Zealand from 1995 to 2009, and was a Member of Parliament from 1996 to 2010. Fitzsimons was also a member of the Alliance Party and Values Party. Fitzsimons died in Thames, New Zealand on 5 March 2020 from a stroke caused by a fall, aged 75. ==References== ==Other websites== * Jeanette Fitzsimons at the Green Party website Category:1945 births Category:2020 deaths Category:Green Party of Aotearoa New Zealand politicians
